00:04:29.017 --> 00:04:32.556
On this side, I have basically,
I do something like this.

00:04:32.556 --> 00:04:35.522
I have the integral of DV.

00:04:35.522 --> 00:04:37.873
This looks like an anti-derivative.

00:04:37.873 --> 00:04:41.155
This is an integral, acting
like an anti-derivative.

00:04:41.155 --> 00:04:44.238
What function has a derivative of DV?

00:04:46.109 --> 00:04:48.553
That would be just plain V.

00:04:48.553 --> 00:04:50.357
I can rewrite this side of the equation,

00:04:50.357 --> 00:04:53.013
constant C comes out of the expression,

00:04:53.013 --> 00:04:54.928
and we end up with V, on this side.

00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.406
Just plain V.

00:04:56.406 --> 00:04:59.156
That equals the integral of I DT.

